  "help_about": "About",
  "help_appInfo": "App to automatically forward incoming SMS messages to a Telegram bot",
  "help_info": "Intro",
  "help_info_01": "The app forwards SMS to a Telegram bot or an email address. You will need your own bot or an email account with SMTP access.",
  "help_info_02": "A forwarding rule is created for each connection — it defines which SMS to send and where. Rules can be duplicated, enabled, or disabled as needed.",
  "help_info_03": "When an SMS arrives, the app checks active rules and attempts to forward it. If it fails due to technical reasons (e.g., no internet), the app will retry later.",
  "help_info_04": "When forwarding SMS from multiple phones, you can set a device label in the settings — it is sent along with the SMS to identify the receiving phone.",
  "help_info_05": "It is recommended to disable battery optimization for the app, since the system may restrict background activity to save power.",
  "help_info_06": "Make sure to keep the internet connection enabled for the app to work.",
  "help_tbot": "Connecting a Telegram Bot",
  "help_tbot_01": "If you don't have a Telegram bot yet, use @BotFather bot to create one and get its token. It's simple and free.",
  "help_tbot_02": "Open a chat with your bot in Telegram, start a conversation, or send any message. This is needed to automatically retrieve the chat id for the next step.",
  "help_tbot_03": "In the app, create a Telegram bot rule and enter the token (you can also set a Chat ID if you know it). Test the settings, then save. A welcome message will arrive upon a successful test.",
  "help_tbot_04": "Done! Everything is set up to forward SMS to your bot. Enable the rule and press Start to begin.",
  "help_smtp": "Connecting an SMTP Server",
  "help_smtp_01": "It is best to create a dedicated email for SMS forwarding (not an alias): it will also serve as your login. This is especially relevant for Gmail and similar services.",
  "help_smtp_02": "Create a rule and fill in the connection details. Usually, an 'App Password' is required (generated in your email provider's security settings).",
  "help_smtp_03": "Test and save the settings, enable the rule, and press Start.",
  "help_filters": "Filters",
  "help_filters_01": "You can set filters for sender or text of incoming SMS messages. A filter is triggered if a sender number/name or text contains the specified characters.",
  "help_filters_02": "There are two modes: whitelist (SMS is forwarded if at least one filter matches) and blacklist (SMS is not forwarded if any filter matches). In whitelist mode, if no filters are set, no SMS messages will be forwarded to the bot.",
  "help_filters_03": "Use two forward slashes for regex. For example, filter /^\\d*555$/ matches all numbers, that end with 555",
  "help_filters_04": "To check whether a specific SMS message will be forwarded based on the current filters, enter the required sender and/or message in the input fields and click the button to verify.",
